WEBVTT

00:01.538 --> 00:12.810
In a season filled with noise, with full calendars, full schedules, and full hands, we can still find ourselves feeling empty.

00:14.111 --> 00:16.754
But Christmas was never meant to be crowded.

00:17.775 --> 00:21.839
It was meant to be clear, simple, uncluttered.

00:23.201 --> 00:28.466
When we make room, we discover the gift that was there all along.

00:33.282 --> 00:34.123
Good morning.

00:35.365 --> 00:36.586
How's everybody doing this morning?

00:37.687 --> 00:40.811
Hey, let me be the first to tell you this morning, Merry Christmas.

00:42.073 --> 00:44.876
Man, we are right in the beginning stages.

00:44.936 --> 00:45.978
It's cold outside.

00:46.278 --> 00:47.179
It feels like winter.

00:47.199 --> 00:49.522
In fact, I walked across the parking lot.

00:49.542 --> 00:53.027
The staff all parks across the street and I literally started singing.

00:53.347 --> 00:56.090
It's beginning to feel a lot like Christmas.

00:56.271 --> 00:57.692
It doesn't look like Christmas.

00:58.053 --> 01:01.277
It's not snowy outside, but man, it feels like Christmas.

01:01.337 --> 01:02.258
It's cold.

01:02.402 --> 01:04.005
Hey, I'm so glad that you're here today.

01:04.025 --> 01:05.166
My name is Pastor Chris.

01:05.647 --> 01:10.275
My wife and I had the honor and the privilege of leading what God's doing through encounter church.

01:10.315 --> 01:11.897
And I'm glad that you're here today.

01:12.298 --> 01:18.949
We are kicking off a brand new series that we're simply calling the uncluttered Christmas.

01:19.029 --> 01:24.578
It's a four week series that will take us up to Christmas and right into Christmas.

01:24.638 --> 01:27.282
But how many of you would agree with me today?

01:27.362 --> 01:38.866
that if we're not careful, we can find ourselves cluttering the Christmas season so much that we lose sight of the real meaning of Christmas.

01:39.714 --> 01:41.116
Come on, let me ask that again.

01:41.176 --> 02:03.823
How many of you would agree with me that if we're not careful, we can find ourselves cluttering Christmas the season so much with details and items and parties and cakes and cookies and all the goodies and all the things that we lose sight of what truly matters for the season?

02:04.885 --> 02:06.066
Here's what I understand.

02:06.914 --> 02:09.838
Christmas isn't about doing more.

02:11.240 --> 02:14.405
It's about making room for what really matters.

02:16.988 --> 02:17.749
And that's Jesus.

02:19.332 --> 02:20.794
I love that song we just sang.

02:20.874 --> 02:23.498
Is there room in your heart?

02:25.220 --> 02:35.154
This Christmas season, I want to encourage you, take a moment amongst the busyness, amongst the chaos, amongst the clutter of Christmas,

02:36.322 --> 02:39.565
Would you just take a moment and slow down?

02:41.026 --> 02:45.571
Take a moment to say, Lord, I give you time.

02:47.092 --> 02:48.493
Lord, I give you myself.

02:49.674 --> 02:51.997
Lord, I give you room in my heart.

02:52.297 --> 02:54.099
I give you room in my life.

02:54.159 --> 02:58.723
I give you room in my family just to move as you desire.

02:58.763 --> 03:06.290
You see, we must choose to clear out the clutter if we desire to make room for Jesus.

03:07.010 --> 03:17.062
In the middle of this culture that is so consumed and truthfully celebrates chaos, it celebrates consumerism.

03:17.122 --> 03:19.625
How many of you went Black Friday shopping?

03:19.665 --> 03:24.130
How many of you went Black Friday shopping online?

03:24.150 --> 03:26.152
Oh, there's some more hands.

03:26.172 --> 03:31.218
Yeah, we went out yesterday as a family and I was looking for two particular items.

03:31.330 --> 03:34.697
I went into Menards and went in there and they had two little boxes.

03:35.057 --> 03:37.522
It's these little car things.

03:37.583 --> 03:39.526
And I was going to pick up a couple of these.

03:39.587 --> 03:40.709
And I asked the lady.

03:40.729 --> 03:41.951
I said, hey, where can I find them?

03:42.312 --> 03:47.042
She says, we only have two left in the store, but they may be in somebody's carts.

03:48.084 --> 03:50.468
I said, I'm about to make this old school Black Friday.

03:50.509 --> 03:51.250
Let's go.

03:53.122 --> 03:56.087
I really, I mean, I said that about those kids.

03:56.347 --> 03:59.232
I ended up finding them on a little rollabout cart.

03:59.372 --> 04:01.755
They're in the middle of the store and I grabbed them and went home.

04:01.936 --> 04:10.048
But I thought back just for a moment, man, kids these days, teenagers these days, they don't even know what Black Friday shopping was.

04:10.789 --> 04:21.426
Come on, how many of you remember getting up at 3.30 in the morning so you could stand in line at Walmart to buy a TV that you didn't need, but it was on sale so you had to have it.

04:22.626 --> 04:26.731
Oh, we still have a TV from like 20 years ago.

04:26.791 --> 04:31.135
I remember going to Cuba, Missouri, little tiny Walmart.

04:31.436 --> 04:33.938
At that point in time, nobody knew the Walmart was there.

04:34.039 --> 04:35.740
So it was easy to go in.

04:35.801 --> 04:36.962
There wasn't a big line.

04:37.002 --> 04:41.687
But as the years went by, people discovered that, hey, I can go to a small Walmart.

04:41.727 --> 04:45.211
So they travel from hours and hours away to go to this little Walmart.

04:45.231 --> 04:51.698
And the very last Black Friday shopping we did there, it was back to back walking like this.

04:52.450 --> 04:59.781
We live in a culture that is consumed with chaos, consumed with consumerism.

05:00.442 --> 05:14.642
But I believe that in this season, Jesus invites us to slow down, to declutter our hearts, to rediscover the peace, the joy, the hope, the love that can only be found in Him.

05:15.554 --> 05:18.860
So over the next four weeks, I wanna dig in to just that.

05:18.940 --> 05:28.197
I wanna take a look at what does it mean to declutter our lives and give it truly, give it all to Jesus?

05:29.740 --> 05:31.023
I need you to do me a favor though.

05:32.024 --> 05:37.234
There are some of you in the room that you're gonna hear the Christmas story for the very first time.

05:37.858 --> 05:42.624
Maybe you grew up in a home where you didn't read the Christmas story on Christmas morning.

05:42.664 --> 05:48.893
Maybe for you, Christmas is just about that overweight guy with the big long beard that kind of jiggles when he laughs.

05:50.475 --> 05:52.097
Don't look at somebody else in the room.

05:53.299 --> 05:55.141
Some heads just kind of turn and look at people.

05:55.201 --> 05:56.002
No, don't do that.

05:56.343 --> 05:59.527
No, some of you, that's what you know of Christmas.

06:01.029 --> 06:07.858
And I would challenge you as we go into this Christmas series, allow God to let his word

06:08.194 --> 06:08.995
become alive.

06:10.096 --> 06:13.820
I believe there's something that we can learn from the Christmas story.

06:14.681 --> 06:26.614
But there are others of you in the room today or maybe even watching online that you've heard these stories, the same Christmas story for 20, 30, 40, 50, 60, 70 years.

06:28.096 --> 06:29.357
I'm going to challenge you.

06:29.377 --> 06:33.682
Wipe that slate clean and allow God to

06:34.082 --> 06:41.289
to bring it to you with a clear set of lenses, with a new perspective this Christmas season.

06:41.409 --> 06:46.053
I believe that God wants to speak into our heart in a real way.

06:46.954 --> 06:48.516
So today, I wanna take a moment.

06:48.856 --> 06:58.445
I wanna look at the first of four areas that need attention as we unclutter or declutter this most wonderful time of the year.

06:58.465 --> 07:03.730
More specifically, I wanna look at a moment when a young teenage girl

07:03.938 --> 07:10.445
Mary has a life-changing encounter with the angel Gabriel.

07:10.485 --> 07:11.586
Take a look at what it says.

07:11.666 --> 07:23.558
And Luke chapter 1, it says, in the sixth month of Elizabeth's pregnancy, God sent the angel Gabriel to Nazareth, a village in Galilee, to a virgin named Mary.

07:24.419 --> 07:28.463
She was engaged to be married to a man named Joseph, a descendant of King David.

07:29.204 --> 07:31.186
Gabriel appeared to her and said,

07:31.330 --> 07:33.912
Greetings, favored woman.

07:33.973 --> 07:36.615
The Lord is with you.

07:37.075 --> 07:38.577
Now hold on to that little sentence.

07:38.597 --> 07:40.979
We're gonna come back to that in just a moment.

07:41.940 --> 07:44.523
Verse 29, confused and disturbed.

07:45.103 --> 07:48.967
Mary tried to think of what the angel could possibly mean.

07:50.088 --> 07:51.009
Don't be afraid, Mary.

07:51.049 --> 07:54.212
The angel told her, for you have found favor with God.

07:55.153 --> 07:59.016
You will conceive and give birth to a son and you will name him Jesus.

07:59.056 --> 08:00.818
He will be very great.

08:00.994 --> 08:02.876
and would be called the son of the Most High.

08:04.078 --> 08:11.407
The Lord God will give him the throne of his ancestor David and he will reign over Israel forever.

08:12.108 --> 08:14.150
His kingdom will never end.

08:15.091 --> 08:17.875
Mary asked the angel, but how can this happen?

08:17.935 --> 08:19.497
I'm a virgin.

08:19.537 --> 08:26.385
The angel replied, the Holy Spirit will come upon you and the power of the Most High will overshadow you.

08:26.425 --> 08:30.610
So the baby to be born will be holy and he will be called

08:30.690 --> 08:31.611
the Son of God.

08:31.671 --> 08:37.878
What's more is your relative Elizabeth has become pregnant in her old age.

08:38.819 --> 08:49.791
People used to say that she was barren, but she has conceived a son and is now in her sixth month for the word of God will never fail.

08:51.192 --> 08:53.275
Mary responded, I am the Lord's servant.

08:54.156 --> 08:57.499
May everything you have said about me come true.

08:58.961 --> 08:59.922
And the angel left her.

09:02.946 --> 09:03.707
I love verse 37.

09:03.727 --> 09:06.331
This is where we're going to rest today.

09:07.874 --> 09:13.362
The Bible says for nothing is impossible with God.

09:13.382 --> 09:16.367
That word nothing, literally it's a word.

09:16.447 --> 09:22.136
It's hard to describe in the English language, but it literally means absolute negative.

09:23.117 --> 09:26.482
There is no more negative than this word.

09:27.183 --> 09:31.410
Nothing is impossible with God.

09:31.618 --> 09:37.305
I want you to look at your situation today because some of us, we use this phrase.

09:37.365 --> 09:41.790
In fact, we'll encourage a friend when a friend's going through a difficult time.

09:42.031 --> 09:46.476
We'll say, hey, just remember, man, nothing's impossible with God.

09:46.556 --> 09:48.398
It's a powerful verse.

09:48.418 --> 09:50.881
It's a great sounding verse.

09:50.921 --> 09:57.970
We quote it quite often, but the problem lies in the fact is when it comes to our personal situation.

09:59.074 --> 10:03.780
Unfortunately, many times we're not sure that it truly applies.

10:05.321 --> 10:05.722
Nothing.

10:08.165 --> 10:12.270
The absolute negative, nothing is impossible for God.

10:12.310 --> 10:12.570
Really?

10:12.610 --> 10:14.933
What about my relationship issues?

10:16.495 --> 10:19.478
What about the financial debacle that we're in right now?

10:20.279 --> 10:22.842
What about that call that I got from the doctor?

10:22.963 --> 10:24.364
What do I do about that?

10:24.424 --> 10:25.906
Well, here's the reality.

10:27.042 --> 10:32.753
Mary didn't know, she didn't truly even understand all that life would send her way.

10:34.276 --> 10:49.906
But what she did know and what she stood upon was the fact, come on, the fact that nothing is or was or ever will be impossible with God.

10:50.690 --> 10:54.495
I'm going to challenge you in this message this morning.

10:54.955 --> 11:03.726
Place yourself in this position of a young teenage girl, suddenly the angel of the Lord Gabriel appears to you.

11:03.766 --> 11:08.331
He says, greetings, you're highly favored.

11:08.351 --> 11:11.995
I got some incredible news for you.

11:12.055 --> 11:17.522
Nothing's impossible with God.

11:19.138 --> 11:27.026
I don't know what you're facing today, but I believe that God is ready and God is willing to pour hope upon your life.

11:28.706 --> 11:51.481
for Mary, whether it was her cousin Elizabeth having a child at a very old age or Mary having a baby when she had never even been with the man, she understood that she had to rest in the fact that nothing was impossible with God, even though these things did not compute in her limited ability of thinking, come on, how many of you know, our ability is limited?

11:51.521 --> 11:57.650
The Bible says that his ways are not our ways, his thoughts are beyond

11:57.890 --> 12:01.994
our thoughts, they're far beyond what we can even comprehend.

12:02.034 --> 12:10.103
But yet in this moment, Mary rested in the fact that nothing was impossible with God.

12:10.143 --> 12:14.608
Such a bizarre, seemingly unexplainable situation.

12:15.749 --> 12:23.358
But Mary chose, as she processed through the clutter, she chose the trust in God.

12:24.058 --> 12:25.360
Oh, look what she says in verse 34.

12:26.061 --> 12:27.442
But how can this happen?

12:28.834 --> 12:31.177
I'm a virgin.

12:31.198 --> 12:37.206
I love the fact that when they're riding the Christmas story, they included moments like this.

12:38.468 --> 12:44.237
They could have just said, hey, the angel Gabriel appeared to Mary and said, greeting favored woman of God.

12:44.417 --> 12:46.901
You're going to have a baby and Mary's like, let's go.

12:49.885 --> 12:53.010
But for many of us, it's been hard to grab ahold of that, wouldn't it?

12:54.402 --> 13:04.458
When we see the human side of Mary, when we see her confusion in her doubt, the Bible says that she was bewildered in her mind.

13:04.498 --> 13:10.507
She struggled in this moment, not doubting God, but doubting the how.

13:12.450 --> 13:15.395
Maybe for you, how's God gonna restore my marriage?

13:18.320 --> 13:19.762
How's God going to

13:20.290 --> 13:22.212
Heal my body or heal my friend.

13:22.773 --> 13:27.819
How's God gonna step in and be Jehovah-Jireh, which means my provider?

13:27.879 --> 13:32.545
How's he gonna be my provider financially or relationally?

13:34.027 --> 13:37.471
How can he get rid of my anxiety and my depression?

13:38.552 --> 13:40.034
How's that even possible?

13:42.537 --> 13:44.139
Mary says, how can this happen?

13:45.761 --> 13:49.586
I'm a virgin, yet suddenly we see in rapid succession

13:50.402 --> 13:56.729
The explanation, the assurance, the angel begins to display all of this to Mary.

13:57.269 --> 13:59.251
In verse 37, he gives the assurance.

13:59.471 --> 14:02.815
He says, God will never fail.

14:02.875 --> 14:05.578
His word will never fail.

14:05.598 --> 14:08.361
Verse 36, he talks about Elizabeth.

14:09.081 --> 14:10.943
He says, you're cousin Elizabeth.

14:11.144 --> 14:13.266
She's old, but she's having a baby.

14:13.286 --> 14:17.330
Come on, may we never be that example.

14:21.858 --> 14:27.366
Come on, somebody, those of you in your 50s, 60s, and 70s, you're like, ah, ah, not today.

14:27.406 --> 14:31.433
She's old, but she's having a baby.

14:31.473 --> 14:36.380
And then this word of assurance falls before her.

14:37.522 --> 14:39.785
Here's what we must understand going into this message.

14:40.126 --> 14:42.770
Your situation may seem overwhelming.

14:44.226 --> 14:47.370
It may seem so bizarre in your mind.

14:47.450 --> 14:50.555
It may seem like there's no hope on the other side.

14:50.595 --> 14:54.880
It may seem like there's no way to find a resolution.

14:54.920 --> 15:03.372
It may seem like you're at an impasse in life, but just as he did this in Mary's life, I want you to know God is still the same.

15:05.214 --> 15:06.035
He's got a hope.

15:07.177 --> 15:08.098
He's got a peace.

15:09.680 --> 15:10.962
He's got a comforts.

15:12.290 --> 15:16.356
Yes, the situation may be different, but our God is the same.

15:17.077 --> 15:19.380
Nothing is impossible for him.

15:20.381 --> 15:22.725
There is hope in Jesus today.

15:22.785 --> 15:25.829
In fact, look at your neighbor today, put it in the chat today.

15:25.889 --> 15:28.192
There is hope in Jesus.

15:29.915 --> 15:38.927
I look this word up this morning just as a little foundation and a biblical form of the word hope because when we hear hope, what do we think?

15:38.947 --> 15:41.010
Well, I hope it works out.

15:41.282 --> 15:44.087
I hope that the resolution comes.

15:44.347 --> 15:46.792
I hope that the marriage is restored.

15:47.132 --> 15:48.014
I hope.

15:48.194 --> 15:52.141
But what does that word look like when we put Jesus in the mix?

15:53.303 --> 15:57.190
Well, hope is often seen as a confident expectation.

15:58.192 --> 15:59.234
Come on.

15:59.254 --> 16:01.778
It's a confident expectation.

16:02.210 --> 16:04.914
It's a trust in God's promises.

16:05.194 --> 16:06.756
It's not just a wishful thinking.

16:06.996 --> 16:14.086
It's a firm assurance that God is faithful and that His plans for us are good.

16:15.768 --> 16:26.162
Today, I want you to offer this moment, offer this situation to God, but in return, would you stand in the confident expectation

16:26.498 --> 16:32.549
that God is going to show up on your behalf, that God will meet you where you are today.

16:34.272 --> 16:34.492
Why?

16:34.572 --> 16:37.277
Because there's hope in Jesus.

16:37.698 --> 16:38.599
But here's the problem.

16:39.741 --> 16:45.051
During this Christmas season, our calendars seem to fill up faster than our hearts do.

16:47.615 --> 16:51.602
If we're being honest, we get cluttered.

16:52.482 --> 16:59.830
We say they weren't just preparing for Christmas, but if we're honest today, most of the time we're preparing for chaos.

16:59.890 --> 17:01.332
We decorate our homes.

17:01.372 --> 17:02.433
We wrap our gifts.

17:02.674 --> 17:08.760
We check off our list, but somewhere along the way, we lose our peace and we lose our hope.

17:10.723 --> 17:13.045
Patience falls to the wayside.

17:14.046 --> 17:15.568
Joy is no longer seen.

17:15.628 --> 17:20.754
The stress load becomes higher than ever before.

17:21.922 --> 17:23.885
this series, The Uncluttered Christmas.

17:24.666 --> 17:34.120
I'm presenting it this year because I believe that God is inviting us, you and I, to slow down and just to make room for Him.

17:34.961 --> 17:37.305
You see, that's been our theme for the year.

17:38.787 --> 17:49.563
To make room in our hearts, to make room in our lives, to make room in His church, to make room in the world, for God to move.

17:49.583 --> 17:51.826
And I believe that the Christmas season

17:52.066 --> 17:52.987
is no different.

17:53.808 --> 18:14.871
Because before there was ever angels and shepherds, before there were ever wise men or gifts, before there was even a manger, there was this young woman named Mary in a small town called Nazareth, who made room in her heart for God to move.

18:14.891 --> 18:18.255
Now, if you keep reading the Christmas story, you get into chapter two.

18:19.076 --> 18:21.298
After all said and done, it says that Mary

18:21.410 --> 18:29.197
took all of these things and she treasured them in her hearts and she thought about them often.

18:30.419 --> 18:31.399
Why did she do that?

18:32.440 --> 18:51.058
Because she had opened up this space and she realized that when she rested in the hope, when she rested in the foundation, in the strength of God, only in those moments can she see herself working through and finding resolution on the other side in the uncluttered situation.

18:51.522 --> 18:54.567
So today I want to give you three truths of an uncluttered hope.

18:54.587 --> 18:55.368
Number one is this.

18:55.668 --> 19:00.175
God often speaks in the midst of our cluttered moments.

19:01.717 --> 19:06.605
Aren't you grateful that God speaks even in the midst of our cluttered mess?

19:07.867 --> 19:08.207
Yes?

19:09.008 --> 19:11.793
I'm just going to talk to this side today because you guys are with me.

19:11.833 --> 19:12.834
You guys are still asleep.

19:13.015 --> 19:14.397
You ate too much turkey.

19:15.598 --> 19:17.782
Come on.

19:17.802 --> 19:20.626
God often speaks in the midst of our cluttered

19:20.770 --> 19:21.412
moments.

19:21.853 --> 19:24.701
I want to step into an amazing story today.

19:24.721 --> 19:32.722
I want us to understand that Mary wasn't in any way expecting or even planning this visit with the angel Gabriel.

19:33.346 --> 19:37.392
She hadn't gone on a weekend spiritual retreat.

19:37.432 --> 19:43.640
She hadn't taken some scrolls and was reading through the Torah and reading with the Word of God.

19:43.860 --> 19:46.584
She wasn't pressing in to the presence of God.

19:46.804 --> 19:49.949
She wasn't kneeling at the altar at the local synagogue.

19:49.969 --> 19:50.509
No, no, no, no.

19:50.750 --> 20:02.706
She was in the midst of her ordinary routine, her regular life, and got interrupted the clutter with something absolutely extraordinary.

20:04.226 --> 20:15.128
Verse 28, the angel Gabriel appeared to her and said, Greetings, favored woman.

20:16.891 --> 20:17.693
The Lord is with you.

20:19.095 --> 20:24.466
Man, there's so much that we can unpack in that little verse alone.

20:26.530 --> 20:27.992
so much that I want us to see.

20:28.012 --> 20:47.783
I don't have time to dig into all of the, but right in the middle of all of the clutter, right in the middle of all the wedding planning and all the chaos of life, the angel Gabriel appears to a poor, young teenage girl.

20:49.004 --> 20:49.725
Two things he says.

20:49.766 --> 20:51.769
Number one, he says greetings.

20:52.490 --> 20:55.314
Now this is more than just a, hello.

20:56.578 --> 20:57.259
Good to see you.

20:57.760 --> 20:58.922
How are things going moment?

20:59.423 --> 21:03.792
This word greeting, it literally, it means be glad.

21:03.832 --> 21:07.920
Rejoice, thrive.

21:07.980 --> 21:11.967
He looks at Mary, he says, be glad.

21:12.007 --> 21:16.756
Rejoice in this moment, thrive in the situation.

21:16.977 --> 21:19.762
You are favored amongst God's people.

21:21.506 --> 21:23.930
I believe that God is saying this to you today.

21:24.130 --> 21:25.392
There are some of you in the room.

21:25.652 --> 21:27.415
You don't feel like thriving.

21:28.817 --> 21:31.682
You feel the way to the world on your shoulders.

21:32.984 --> 21:36.509
But I want you to hear the second thing that the angel Gabriel said to Mary.

21:39.073 --> 21:43.621
He said, greetings favored woman.

21:46.265 --> 21:49.650
Greetings favored woman.

21:53.058 --> 21:56.704
Many of us seemingly have lost our hope and our joy.

21:59.849 --> 22:03.475
We, we seem like we don't know how to move on.

22:03.535 --> 22:13.232
We don't see, we seem like we don't know how to go to that next step because our, our clutter has, have you ever watched that show, um, hoarders?

22:17.980 --> 22:18.080
Wow.

22:18.100 --> 22:19.442
It's overwhelming, isn't it?

22:21.122 --> 22:28.593
Man, you watch the show and you walk into the house and all there is is a pathway around because things are piled.

22:28.954 --> 22:30.997
Some of us, that's our lives.

22:31.277 --> 22:40.330
It may not physically be there, but emotionally, relationally, in every other way we're consumed.

22:40.350 --> 22:44.256
There are piles of things all around us.

22:46.119 --> 22:48.242
Many of us, Christians included,

22:48.642 --> 22:51.812
have embraced the distractions of the world.

22:52.193 --> 22:55.222
We live in this vacuum of chaos.

22:57.168 --> 23:03.186
Unfortunately, some of us even seek out chaos because that's the order that we know.

23:03.938 --> 23:11.411
I want to challenge you today in the midst of this chaotic season, allow God to speak into the cluttered moments of your life.

23:11.592 --> 23:14.737
Allow Him to renew a joy inside of you.

23:14.777 --> 23:20.948
Allow Him to bring you to the place of not just existing, but a thriving in Him.

23:21.088 --> 23:21.329
Why?

23:21.569 --> 23:24.515
Because you are favored amongst God's people.

23:25.997 --> 23:28.722
Some translations say highly favored.

23:29.794 --> 23:33.337
This particular word has a blessing wrapped around it.

23:33.357 --> 23:35.459
It's honor and it's grace.

23:36.761 --> 23:41.225
Maybe you're here and you're like, you know, I don't know that I can step into that.

23:42.486 --> 23:49.833
Well, if you're a child of God, if you've given your life to Jesus Christ, you're not only favored, but you're so much more.

23:50.934 --> 23:54.457
It's time to step into what God has called for you.

23:54.497 --> 23:56.599
Notice what happened next.

23:57.340 --> 23:59.602
Mary was greatly troubled.

23:59.746 --> 24:01.488
What kind of greeting this might be?

24:01.508 --> 24:04.192
In other words, what's happening right now?

24:06.014 --> 24:12.041
See, there wasn't anybody that Mary could go to and say, hey, do you remember the last time Gabriel showed up to you?

24:12.362 --> 24:13.383
What was that like?

24:16.607 --> 24:22.094
You know that time and a big tall angel showed up in your room and said that you were favored?

24:22.134 --> 24:25.618
What did you feel at that moment?

24:27.202 --> 24:30.647
No, Mary, in that moment, she was cast out in her mind.

24:30.707 --> 24:35.994
The Bible says she couldn't quite wrap herself around what was going on.

24:37.836 --> 24:39.178
But here's what I love about God.

24:39.399 --> 24:41.742
He doesn't always wait for us to slow down.

24:43.424 --> 24:47.910
But right in the middle of our mess, he chooses to speak.

24:49.693 --> 24:51.796
I can hear some of your arguments this morning.

24:52.857 --> 24:56.562
You're saying things like this, well, I haven't heard God talk to me in quite some time.

24:57.922 --> 24:59.905
Could it be that we haven't made room for him?

25:05.372 --> 25:18.370
Could it be that we haven't just said, Lord, I give you this moment, but we're running from one fire to the next, one chaotic moment to the next?

25:19.932 --> 25:26.962
We say things like, well, I'll hear from God when life comes down, but what if God is saying, you'll hear from me,

25:27.234 --> 25:39.351
When you slow down, regardless what life is doing, this uncluttered moment with God starts when we pause long enough to simply listen to Him.

25:41.314 --> 25:45.439
The psalmist said it this way, be still and know that I am God.

25:47.743 --> 25:48.303
Be still.

25:51.468 --> 25:55.954
When is the last time that you just turned off the noise?

25:59.234 --> 26:02.418
When's the last time that you put down the phone?

26:04.340 --> 26:06.804
Better yet, when's the last time you turned off the phone?

26:08.345 --> 26:13.212
You know, they say that electronics is good every once in a while to reboot them because it kind of refreshes.

26:13.272 --> 26:15.414
I believe the same thing goes for us.

26:15.474 --> 26:17.297
Sometimes we need a good reboot.

26:19.880 --> 26:21.542
We need to disconnect.

26:22.523 --> 26:24.626
I used to struggle with that heavily.

26:25.346 --> 26:35.581
I remember when I was in St. Charles, I had a laptop and I would take that laptop with me everywhere and at home, we'd be sitting together as a family and I'd be working on my laptop into the evening.

26:35.841 --> 26:36.803
Yeah, I'm with you.

26:36.883 --> 26:37.924
Yep, yep, yep.

26:37.944 --> 26:38.585
I'm still working.

26:38.625 --> 26:39.587
I'm talking to the family.

26:39.607 --> 26:40.989
I'm still here, but I'm working.

26:41.009 --> 26:42.671
I'm not disconnected.

26:42.691 --> 26:44.534
I was plugged in all the time.

26:44.834 --> 26:48.259
When I moved here, I said, I don't want a laptop.

26:49.140 --> 26:50.182
I have no self-control.

26:51.644 --> 26:53.106
Okay, can I just be transparent with you?

26:53.698 --> 26:59.264
About seven years I went with a desktop because I knew that if I had a laptop, it would go with me and I would work.

27:01.126 --> 27:04.310
About seven years later, I can now honestly take my laptop home.

27:04.730 --> 27:05.571
I don't open it.

27:07.213 --> 27:07.574
I don't.

27:09.235 --> 27:10.076
Now I got my phone.

27:10.096 --> 27:13.961
If emergency, I can get to something, but I'm not going to be working.

27:14.742 --> 27:17.845
I'm going to take some time just to decompress my mind.

27:17.885 --> 27:22.130
I remember one of the very first big vacations we took as a family.

27:23.330 --> 27:26.134
We went to a beach and we were hanging out at the beach.

27:26.475 --> 27:31.102
In fact, we were on an island, a Sanibel Island, right off coast of Florida.

27:31.122 --> 27:34.366
And we were in this condo and we were going to the beach every day.

27:34.426 --> 27:40.716
Basically our agenda was beach, pool, eat, beach, pool, eat, nap, beach, pool, eat, nap.

27:40.736 --> 27:41.857
And that was kind of the agenda.

27:42.258 --> 27:46.384
And it took me to talk about Wednesday of that week to realize this is okay.

27:47.986 --> 27:53.074
Because we have geared our lives so much to be accustomed

27:53.346 --> 28:02.640
to chaos that we run on thriving, we run on just this high fight or flight moments all the time.

28:02.660 --> 28:04.042
But we weren't created for that.

28:05.163 --> 28:08.328
The Sabbath, the Bible says, which created for us.

28:09.530 --> 28:18.863
We need moments of rest, moments just to be still and know that he is God, to allow God to speak into our lives.

28:19.624 --> 28:20.786
Number two is this.

28:21.954 --> 28:27.001
If we allow it, our faith can create space for God to move.

28:27.261 --> 28:32.348
If we allow it, our faith can create space for God to move.

28:32.749 --> 28:36.293
Now, what was Mary's original response?

28:37.195 --> 28:38.356
Maybe a little bit confusion.

28:38.436 --> 28:43.023
Perhaps a little bit of doubt or uncertainty.

28:43.063 --> 28:47.969
No doubt there was fear that raised up inside of her.

28:47.989 --> 28:51.474
I don't know about you, but that...

28:54.466 --> 28:56.288
because this is often our response.

28:56.989 --> 29:03.759
God tries to speak into our lives and suddenly we come up with all the reasons why this just can't be true.

29:04.820 --> 29:07.904
We build walls of fear, we build walls of doubt.

29:08.045 --> 29:10.147
Surely this is not possible.

29:10.167 --> 29:20.281
Look what it says in verse 29, confused and disturbed, Mary tried to think what the angel could mean, verse 34.

29:21.523 --> 29:23.826
Mary asked the angel, but how can this happen?

29:24.418 --> 29:25.099
I'm a virgin.

29:26.300 --> 29:26.881
Understand this.

29:27.822 --> 29:31.185
Mary did not deny what God was saying.

29:32.747 --> 29:33.808
She just didn't understand.

29:35.249 --> 29:39.293
She couldn't wrap herself around how this could happen.

29:39.754 --> 29:51.506
She had to choose in the moment to make room for God to move in her life, in her clutter, in every moment, every situation.

29:53.026 --> 29:59.515
She had to come to the place of saying, Lord, I don't know the how, but I know the who.

30:00.997 --> 30:02.359
See, that's where we get stuck.

30:03.260 --> 30:06.304
How in the world is this going to work out?

30:06.344 --> 30:11.291
We say things like, well, I know that God can, but how will he?

30:11.311 --> 30:17.740
I know that God is able, but how's this gonna work out?

30:17.860 --> 30:19.682
Listen to the angel Gabriel's response.

30:20.443 --> 30:22.386
The Holy Spirit will come upon you.

30:22.530 --> 30:25.072
and the power of the most high will overshadow you.

30:25.393 --> 30:27.475
So the baby to be born will be holy.

30:27.515 --> 30:30.117
He will be called the son of God, verse 37.

30:30.177 --> 30:33.701
For nothing is impossible with God.

30:34.221 --> 30:35.102
Come on, hold on to that.

30:35.322 --> 30:38.886
For nothing is impossible with God.

30:38.966 --> 30:43.470
God not only has the how, but he has the ability.

30:45.192 --> 30:46.353
Come on, let me say that again.

30:46.373 --> 30:51.858
God not only has the how, but he has the ability.

30:52.770 --> 30:54.252
How did Mary respond?

30:55.414 --> 31:00.041
Well, she quickly began to unclutter the moment she made space.

31:00.101 --> 31:03.586
And the verse 38 says, Mary responded, I am the Lord servant.

31:03.827 --> 31:07.812
May everything you have said about me come true.

31:09.215 --> 31:10.356
Come on, that's bold faith.

31:12.159 --> 31:14.182
That that's uncluttered faith.

31:14.322 --> 31:19.570
She didn't say, Lord, if you will give me the full detailed explanation.

31:20.802 --> 31:37.125
God, if you will lay out all this, God, if you'll put this on a PowerPoint presentation and present this in the moment, God, if you'll just make a Zoom link, we'll get together, we'll talk about this, you can bring it, we'll share screens, we can talk about this.

31:37.425 --> 31:44.535
If you'll just lay this out for me, God, maybe then, maybe then, God, I can wrap myself around this.

31:44.576 --> 31:46.198
Mary didn't say any of that.

31:47.440 --> 31:49.202
She just said, I'm the Lord's servants.

31:50.754 --> 31:52.177
She didn't try to take control.

31:52.237 --> 31:55.925
She didn't create a backup plan in case it didn't work.

31:57.448 --> 32:00.715
She made space for God to move.

32:02.017 --> 32:03.020
Now here's the reality.

32:03.200 --> 32:06.647
Fear says, what if it doesn't work?

32:06.667 --> 32:08.050
Come on, have you ever said that before?

32:09.666 --> 32:21.317
Yeah, every one of us, I'm certain every one of us in the room at some moment, at some point, at some time in our lives, God calls us to a situation and we say things like, well, what if it doesn't work?

32:25.341 --> 32:38.194
And I've had that thought a lot as we've stepped out in faith as we launched our second location in Wardsburg in 2021 coming out of a pandemic.

32:40.354 --> 32:42.678
The board and I had had a lot of conversations in 2020.

32:42.798 --> 32:49.969
How are we going to raise funds when we're RSVP into church?

32:51.070 --> 32:53.254
How are we going to raise funds when we're social distance?

32:53.274 --> 32:57.941
We only have 106 seats in here and we're running three services trying to get everybody in.

32:58.161 --> 32:59.603
How are we going to raise funds?

32:59.623 --> 33:01.386
How are we going to launch another location?

33:01.586 --> 33:02.828
What if it doesn't work?

33:06.013 --> 33:09.138
No doubt the same thought when we went to Lincoln.

33:11.906 --> 33:13.067
We weren't taking over a church.

33:13.087 --> 33:14.329
We were starting a church.

33:15.650 --> 33:17.712
We were renovating a dollar general building.

33:17.752 --> 33:18.633
Come on, somebody.

33:19.474 --> 33:23.919
By the way, I can't even drive past dollar general anymore without going, that should be a church.

33:25.981 --> 33:29.765
I mean, is it wrong to pray the dollar general goes out of business so we can have the building?

33:31.267 --> 33:32.548
Dollar general, I love you.

33:32.568 --> 33:33.850
I call you dollar general.

33:34.270 --> 33:35.972
I love you, but we're not praying you out of business.

33:35.992 --> 33:38.034
But if you have a building open, give me a call.

33:38.914 --> 33:42.118
Yeah, yeah, so I see these buildings, but what if it doesn't work?

33:42.158 --> 33:43.359
What if it doesn't pan out?

33:43.379 --> 33:44.200
What if it doesn't?

33:44.220 --> 33:45.502
We're getting ready to build a building here.

33:45.702 --> 33:46.663
What if it doesn't work?

33:47.845 --> 34:00.500
Man, I spent a couple of days this week budgeting for 2026, and I'm crunching the numbers, and I'm doing thoughts of if we have a tied increase of this, or if this occurs, and then the thought crosses my mind.

34:00.700 --> 34:02.162
But what if it doesn't work?

34:04.034 --> 34:07.338
You see, fear builds up these barriers in life.

34:07.578 --> 34:09.200
Fear says, what if it doesn't work?

34:09.220 --> 34:10.542
What if God doesn't show up?

34:12.044 --> 34:18.231
Faith says, what if God shows up?

34:18.251 --> 34:20.594
What if God actually follows through?

34:20.654 --> 34:26.561
What if God does what he says he will do?

34:28.684 --> 34:33.650
When I moved here in 2012, church was running about 65 people

34:34.498 --> 34:35.439
just one location.

34:36.942 --> 34:43.893
And God placed a vision upon my heart, not a literal vision where I saw things, but a vision in my heart.

34:44.794 --> 34:48.540
And He brought me back to the scriptures where it says, I'm about to do something new.

34:48.560 --> 34:53.548
In fact, that was the very first scripture text that I read in this building.

34:55.051 --> 34:56.393
It says, I'm about to do something new.

34:56.433 --> 34:58.796
I want you to forget all the things that I've done.

34:58.837 --> 35:00.960
I'm doing something new.

35:01.060 --> 35:02.322
Don't you see it.

35:03.874 --> 35:07.718
I had to come to the place that I said, Lord, I trust you.

35:09.380 --> 35:12.563
Lord, I'm gonna allow you in the midst of the chaos of my life.

35:12.603 --> 35:15.326
God, I'm gonna allow you, Lord, to speak into my life.

35:15.346 --> 35:20.952
Lord, I'm gonna open the door by faith to allow your hope to enter in.

35:21.012 --> 35:26.979
See, faith is what helps us to step out of the clutter and into his presence.

35:27.019 --> 35:33.586
Psalms chapter 16, verse 11 reminds us that it's in his presence that we will experience

35:33.730 --> 35:34.772
fullness of joy.

35:34.812 --> 35:39.442
Some of us, we don't experience the fullness of joy.

35:39.682 --> 35:44.392
We don't experience the peace of God because we're not hanging out in His presence.

35:47.558 --> 35:47.859
Amen.

35:51.086 --> 35:53.170
It's got to encourage yourself every now and again.

35:53.730 --> 35:54.992
Come on, Ron, you're not doing it.

35:55.012 --> 35:55.773
Somebody's got you.

35:55.793 --> 35:57.114
I'm just going to encourage myself today.

35:57.475 --> 36:01.781
Sometimes we got to physically move out of the chaotic moment.

36:01.961 --> 36:04.104
We got to step out of the cluttered mess.

36:04.304 --> 36:14.197
We got to step into the presence of God because then and only then will we begin to experience the fullness of His joy and the hope that He gives us.

36:14.217 --> 36:21.106
Truth number three, very quickly, hope is established when we trust God above our worries.

36:22.466 --> 36:28.115
Hope is established when we trust God above our worries.

36:28.155 --> 36:36.587
Now I purposely use the word establish here because it means this, to set on a firm or permanent basis.

36:37.669 --> 36:41.254
It's saying, Lord, I'm not gonna waver in this.

36:41.395 --> 36:46.322
Though the winds may blow, though the waters may rise.

36:47.938 --> 36:50.361
Though I may be pressed on every side.

36:50.621 --> 36:58.431
God, I'm not going to lose hope because I'm standing firm on the foundation of who you are.

36:59.872 --> 37:01.855
Mary didn't get all the answers that day.

37:01.895 --> 37:04.718
Oh, she would still face the questions.

37:06.020 --> 37:08.323
No doubt there was gossip running wild.

37:09.284 --> 37:12.327
She wasn't sure how Joseph was going to respond.

37:12.347 --> 37:14.450
Could you imagine that conversation?

37:16.162 --> 37:20.288
but she chose to believe God's word over her worries.

37:22.331 --> 37:24.334
I want you to look at your clutter today.

37:26.136 --> 37:35.009
In what way could you or in what way should you choose to trust God more than the clutter?

37:36.250 --> 37:42.960
Setting the clutter to the side, the worry, the doubts and choosing today to follow after him.

37:43.020 --> 37:44.562
I remember the old song,

37:44.642 --> 37:46.044
We used to sing when I was a kid.

37:46.064 --> 37:48.908
I have decided to follow Jesus.

37:50.129 --> 37:56.778
Though none will follow, though none go with me, I still will follow.

37:58.300 --> 38:02.966
I never want to become guilty of leaning into stuff more than I lean into God.

38:03.026 --> 38:09.234
I never want to be guilty of trusting stuff and trusting the clutter more than I trust in God.

38:11.618 --> 38:14.742
It's not pretending that everything's okay.

38:15.924 --> 38:21.512
It's trusting that God's promise is still true even when life is uncertain.

38:24.376 --> 38:33.729
You see, even when you don't have the answers, it's resting in the reality that nothing is impossible with God.

38:33.749 --> 38:34.770
Grab ahold of this.

38:34.946 --> 38:45.965
For every reason Mary had to doubt, for every fear that she had about the future, God already had a plan.

38:49.872 --> 38:58.226
For every fear you may have, for every doubt that you've conjured up in your mind,

38:58.562 --> 39:02.529
for every reason you've come up with that it just cannot work.

39:02.870 --> 39:08.019
I want you to know today that God already has a plan.

39:09.542 --> 39:15.553
You may not understand it and that's okay because the Bible says trust in the Lord with all your heart.

39:17.116 --> 39:18.238
Don't lean on what?

39:18.899 --> 39:20.402
Your own understanding.

39:22.082 --> 39:25.447
Don't lean on your ability to comprehend.

39:25.487 --> 39:32.538
Don't lean on your ability to have it figured out, but trust in God with all of your hearts.

39:34.381 --> 39:39.769
So this Christmas, don't let your heart get buried in the clutter.

39:41.011 --> 39:45.618
Remember, Mary took all of this and she hid it in her heart.

39:46.690 --> 39:54.642
Don't allow this most wonderful time of the year to become overrun with the busyness and the chaos of life.

39:54.862 --> 40:00.390
Don't allow all the stuff of the season to drown out the sound of God's voice.

40:02.473 --> 40:06.099
I believe that it's time for us to unclutter our hearts.

40:07.200 --> 40:10.465
It's time for us to make room for God.

40:11.647 --> 40:16.594
Because when you do, you'll find that the same God who spoke to Mary still speaks

40:16.802 --> 40:23.870
today, the same God who filled her life with promise was to fill your life with hope.

40:25.712 --> 40:32.679
Matthew chapter 12 says it this way, and his name will be the hope of all the world.

40:34.702 --> 40:36.844
There's hope in the name of Jesus.

40:38.966 --> 40:46.034
You see some of us in the midst of our clutter, we need to pause just for a moment and say Jesus.

40:48.866 --> 40:57.617
Jesus, be the God of peace, be the God of hope.

41:00.280 --> 41:06.727
Jesus will help us to establish this faith in you.

41:09.871 --> 41:18.802
Jesus, when we come back to where we started today, for nothing is impossible.

41:20.578 --> 41:24.242
with you, Jesus.

41:25.563 --> 41:26.984
Come on, would you say His name with me today?

41:27.765 --> 41:31.049
Jesus, Jesus.

41:33.011 --> 41:44.482
There's hope, there's power, there's comforts, there's deliverance, there's joy in the name of Jesus.

41:46.504 --> 41:48.306
Lord, speak it to our hearts right now.

41:49.922 --> 41:57.344
Lord, calm the chaos, unclutter the noise, clean out the mess.

41:59.351 --> 42:00.895
Lord, help us to make room for you.

42:03.062 --> 42:04.466
In Jesus' name we pray.

